5|$|Since the {{adoption}} of the article of faith on the baptism of the <b>Holy</b> <b>Spirit</b> in 1908, the Pentecostal Holiness Church has taught the following beliefs as their five cardinal doctrines: justification by faith, entire sanctification, the baptism in the <b>Holy</b> <b>Spirit</b> evidenced by speaking in tongues, Christ's atonement (including divine healing), and the premillennial second coming of Christ.|$|E
